column5: I finally found it!South end of the Tug Channel, looking south on the east side. A beautiful, gorgeous, splendid Ontario fall afternoon
I was in that same area about that time of year.....35 years ago!!!
from Clearwater Bay, Corkscrew Island area.
Thank you. The post will go up on the Facebook page at 7:00 pm tonight https://www.facebook.com/NoNuclearWasteInNWO

I am looking for a couple of good quality pictures taken on the Lake of the Woods to use on a Facebook post. These do not necessarily have to be of fish, they can be a scene on the lake. If you have 1 or 2 you would not mind sharing, please post them on this thread, or message me with them. Thanks for the help.
Skywagon on FB? Say it isn't so...........Pooch
Same location looking east. Don't know why it's upside down.
Booze caused that,did you fall down when you took the picture.lol
Hah! Nope, was right side up when I uploaded it 🤔

Sad isn't it? Pooch, if it helps I just got back from the cabin doing manly things, like staining the sauna building. The Facebook post has to do with the high-level nuclear waste dump they want to put in our area. Lake of the Woods is in the watershed downstream from where they want to bury the nuclear waste. For those brave enough to be on Facebook, here is the page that will have the post- https://www.facebook.com/NoNuclearWasteInNWO
